IQA Diatomic "Interaction" Energy Components:
--------------------------------------------
  E_IQA_Inter(A,B) = Vne(A,B) + Ven(A,B) + Vee(A,B) + Vnn(A,B)
                   = Total IQA "Interaction" Energy Between Atoms A and B
  Vne(A,B) = Ven(B,A) = Attraction Energy Between Nucleus of Atom A and Electron Density Distribution of Atom B
  Ven(A,B) = Vne(B,A) = Attraction Energy Between Electron Density Distribution of Atom A and Nucleus of Atom B
  Vee(A,B) = Two-electron Interaction Energy Between Atom A and Atom B
  Vnn(A,B) = Repulsion Energy Between Nucleus of Atom A and Nucleus of Atom B
  VeeC(A,B) = Coulomb Part of Vee(A,B)
  VeeX(A,B) = Exchange-Correlation Part of Vee(A,B)
See "2EDM Note" and "DFT Note".
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
